{
  "baseline_date": "2026-03-23",
  "step": "Inspect `codex-dashboard/server.js` and `codex-dashboard/index.html` to inventory the exact dashboard data sources, rendered sections, and existing fields already related to approvals, execution history, retries, scores, timestamps, and manual recovery; write a compact JSON baseline note that names the reusable fields for security, audit, and governance panels.",
  "sources": {
    "server_file": "codex-dashboard/server.js",
    "ui_file": "codex-dashboard/index.html",
    "live_endpoints_used_by_ui": [
      "/api/projects",
      "/api/status",
      "/api/logs",
      "/api/metrics",
      "/api/queue",
      "/api/task-registry"
    ],
    "operator_action_endpoints_used_by_ui": [
      "POST /api/task-registry",
      "POST /api/task-registry/intake",
      "POST /api/task-registry/update",
      "POST /api/task-registry/action",
      "POST /api/retry-last-failed"
    ],
    "notes": [
      "`index.html` fetches `/api/metrics` for sidebar metrics and retry availability.",
      "`index.html` fetches `/api/task-registry` for task board cards, summary counts, approval state, execution details, history preview, handoff details, and timestamps.",
      "`index.html` fetches `/api/projects` to populate the intake project selector and posts both scoped task submissions and prompt-intake derivations back through the task-registry APIs.",
      "`index.html` reads prompt-intake capability and approval-block context from `/api/status`, then disables or enables prompt intake and retry controls based on that runtime state.",
      "Manual recovery is counted in persisted metrics generation, but `readMetrics()` does not currently expose `manual_recovery_records` on `/api/metrics`."
    ]
  },
